raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "certbot-nginx" %}
{% set version = "1.29.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/certbot-nginx-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5a8837c01e36287bd9959d46001883c5c6edb7f05e94de1d80992e547dc9a927

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.7
  run:
    - acme >={{ version }}
    - certbot >={{ version }}
    - pyopenssl >=17.5.0
    - pyparsing >=2.2.1
    - python >=3.7
    - setuptools >=41.6.0

test:
  imports:
    - certbot_nginx
    - certbot_nginx._internal
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt
  summary: Nginx plugin for Certbot
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nehaljwani
